  "slug": "where-does-the-autonomy-wobble-live-journal",
  "title": "Where Does the Autonomy Wobble Live?",
  "subtitle": "A journal prompt set for locating the specific moments, amounts, and categories where financial independence feels shakiest within a partnership",
  "excerpt": "A journal prompt set for the stuck-on feeling of financial smallness when a partner earns. The prompts locate exactly where the wobble lives: which spending triggers guilt, which decisions feel like they need approval, so the pattern becomes clear and workable.",
  "type": "PRACTICE",
  "sourceNotes": "Original journal prompts written for homemade.education.",
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A journal prompt set for the feeling that money in a partnership is not fully yours to use. The prompts do not assume the relationship is the problem. They locate where the pattern lives inside you, so you can work with it directly.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "New to journal prompts as practice? Read ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "journal prompts as practice",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "/mindset/journal-prompts-as-practice"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " first.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The practice",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Warm-up",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 4
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "What is the spending category where you feel least entitled to use shared money freely?",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Name the category. Write why that one in particular.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 4
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Is there an amount above which spending starts to feel like it requires permission?",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Write the number. Write where you think that number came from.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Closer in",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 4
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "What would financial autonomy look like, practically, in this partnership?",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Write the concrete version: an account, an amount, an agreement, a decision you could make without checking first.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 4
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "What did you see modelled about money and partnership growing up?",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Write what you observed. Write whether you are still living it.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 4
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "What is the one financial decision you have been delaying because it does not feel like yours to make?",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Name it. Write what would change if you made it anyway.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where this practice comes from",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Written for homemade.education.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
